================================================================================
 Author: Chris Wozniak
 Course: CPSC525

 This program creates a child thread, then uses ptrace() to set the 'rip'
 register (program counter) to point past the guards in helloworld-x86_64

================================================================================
1. Run make to build the "exploit" program
	
	make

2. Run the exploit, this should print "Hello world!" regardless of what
   values are in file1, file2, file3, file4.
	
	./exploit

================================================================================

